Hi Adrian -<br><br>Thanks for the reply.&nbsp; I have been investigating this further.&nbsp; It appears that ssh isn&#39;t starting my .zshrc file.&nbsp; This is strange.&nbsp; <br><br>If I execute<br><br>&gt; ssh host-0 export<br><br>I get only a minimal set of environment variables.&nbsp; One of them is SHELL = /bin/zsh.&nbsp; There is no LD_LIBRARY_PATH in the list.
<br><br>If I ssh into host-0 and type &quot;export&quot;, I get my full list of variables.<br><br>Seeing as how this is almost certainly an ssh problem, I should probably take this to the openssh mailing list.<br><br>Thanks,
