On Tue, Jan 16, 2007 at 05:22:35PM -0800, Brian Budge wrote:<br><br>&gt; Hi all -<br><br>Hi!<br><br>&gt; If I run from host-0:<br>&gt; &gt; mpirun -np 4 -host host-0 myprogram<br>&gt;<br>&gt; I have no problems, but if I run
<br>&gt; &gt;mpirun -np 4 -host host-1 myprogram<br>&gt; error while loading shared libraries: libSGUL.so: cannot open shared<br>&gt; object file: No such file or directory<br><br>&gt; &gt;mpirun -np 1 -host host-1 ldd myprogram
<br>&gt;<br>&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; libSGUL.so =&gt; not found<br>&gt;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; libOpenMesh_Core.so =&gt; not found<br><br>Obviously, you&#39;ll need these libs on host-1. Even more, they need<br>to be found in a system library dir (
e.g. /usr/lib) or somewhere<br>inside LD_LIBRARY_PATH. I guess you already know that.<br><br>&gt; If I run the following, however, I see that my LD_LIBRARY_PATH is correct:<br>&gt; &gt; mpirun -np 1 -host burn-0 echo $LD_LIBRARY_PATH
<br><br>The variable is expanded on the calling host:<br><br>adi@ipc654:~$ echo $HOSTNAME<br>ipc654<br>adi@ipc654:~$ mpirun -np 1 -host amun3 echo $HOSTNAME<br>ipc654<br><br>In other words: you&#39;re echoing your local LD_LIBRARY_PATH. If this
<br>should be the same on host-1, either set it in your login scripts<br>(on host-1) or export it with -x:<br><br>host-0:~$ mpirun -x LD_LIBRARY_PATH -host host-1 your_prog<br><br><br>HTH<br><br>--<br>Cluster and Metacomputing Working Group
